revision.text:
A '''democratic intervention''' is a [[military intervention]] by external forces with the aim of assisting [[democratization]] of the country where the intervention takes place. Examples include [[Interventionism (politics)|intervention]] in Afghanistan and Iraq.<ref>{{cite journal | last1 =Merkel | first1 =Wolfgang | last2 = Grimm  | first2 =Sonja | title =War and Democratization: Legality, Legitimacy and Effectiveness  | journal = Democratization  | year =2008 | month = | volume =15 | issue =3 | pages =457-471 | url =https://dx.doi.org/10.1080/13510340801991072 }}</ref>

