{{Infobox journal | title = Pacific Philosophical Quarterly | cover = | editor = Faculty of the School of Philosophy at the [[University of Southern California]] | discipline = [[Philosophy]] | abbreviation = Pac. Philos. Q. | formernames = The Personalist | publisher = [[Wiley-Blackwell]] on behalf of the School of Philosophy at the University of Southern California | country = United States | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1920–present | openaccess = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/journal/10.1111/(ISSN)1468-0114 | link1 = http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/journal/10.1111/(ISSN)1468-0114/currentissue | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/journal/10.1111/(ISSN)1468-0114/issues | link2-name = Online archive | JSTOR = | OCLC = 06272734 | LCCN = 83641258 | CODEN = PPHQEJ | ISSN = 0279-0750 | eISSN = 1468-0114 }} The '''''Pacific Philosophical Quarterly''''' is a quarterly [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] of [[philosophy]] published by [[Wiley-Blackwell]] on behalf of the School of Philosophy ([[University of Southern California]]) and is edited by the faculty there. The journal covers all major areas of philosophy in the [[analytic philosophy|analytic tradition]], sometimes as special issues aimed at a particular topic.
==History== The journal was established in 1920 as '''''The Personalist''''' by [[Ralph Tyler Flewelling]] and focused on the philosophy of [[personalism]]. It obtained its current name in 1980<ref>''One Hundred Twentieth-Century Philosophers'', edited by Stuart C. Brown, Diané Collinson, and Robert Wilkinson, (Routledge, 1998) p. 226.</ref> and "devoted itself exclusively to analytical and logical philosophy".<ref>[http://www.siu.edu/~tpf/ "An Editorial Statement on the Transition Between Journals"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080515160903/http://www.siu.edu/%7Etpf/ |date=2008-05-15 }}, Randall E. Auxier, accessed 10 Aug. 2008.</ref>
